==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eleemosynary
<hw>El`ee*mos"y*na*ry</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>eleemosynarius</ets>, fr. <ets>eleemosyna</ets> alms, Gr. <?/ alms.
See <er>Alms</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to charity, alms, or
almsgiving; intended for the distribution of charity; <as>as, an
<ex>eleemosynary</ex> corporation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Given in charity or alms; having the nature of alms;
<as>as, <ex>eleemosynary</ex> assistance</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Eleemosynary</xex> cures.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Supported by charity; <as>as, <ex>eleemosynary</ex>
poor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eleemosynary</ent>⟦br⟧

